<div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-12 lg:items-start">
  <div class="lg:col-span-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Resources</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
      These are practical “what do I do next?” pathways. We avoid posting phone numbers that change—use the linked
      official sites or search the organization name + “non-emergency” for current contact details.
    </p>

    <section id="official-sites" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Local sites (optional: Utah / Cache County)</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        These links go directly to official agency websites for a specific region. Replace with your local agencies if
        you live elsewhere.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <a
          class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm hover:border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900 dark:hover:border-slate-700"
          href="https://www.loganutah.gov/government/departments/police/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-bold">Logan City Police Department</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Official city police page (contact + services).</p>
        </a>
        <a
          class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm hover:border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900 dark:hover:border-slate-700"
          href="https://www.cachecounty.gov/sheriffs-office/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-bold">Cache County Sheriff’s Office</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Official sheriff’s office page (general info).</p>
        </a>
        <a
          class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm hover:border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900 dark:hover:border-slate-700"
          href="https://www.usu.edu/police/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-bold">Utah State University Police</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Campus safety and reporting resources.</p>
        </a>
        <a
          class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm hover:border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900 dark:hover:border-slate-700"
          href="https://www.cachecounty.gov/victim-services/identity-theft.html"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-bold">Cache County Victim Services (Identity Theft)</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">County resource page for identity theft victims.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="immediate-danger" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Immediate danger</h2>
      <div
        class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-6 text-amber-950 dark:border-amber-900/60 dark:bg-amber-950/40 dark:text-amber-100"
      >
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
          If you are in immediate danger, call <strong>911</strong>. If you are not in immediate danger but need to
          report a crime, use your local agency’s non-emergency contact.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="harassment" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Harassment, stalking, threats</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900">
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-3 pl-5 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          <li>
            <strong>Preserve evidence</strong>: screenshots, message exports, URLs, and dates/times. Write a short
            timeline.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Secure your core accounts</strong>: email + phone number + Apple/Google. See
            <a class="underline underline-offset-4" href="/device-security#feel-monitored">Device Security</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Report via official channels</strong>: contact your local law enforcement agency (non-emergency if
            appropriate). Use official websites to find current contact details.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Consider protective steps</strong>: document incidents, review home privacy (address exposure), and
            share your situation with a trusted person.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="fraud" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Fraud & identity theft</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900">
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          Start with the FTC resources—they provide a step-by-step plan and documents you can use with banks and credit
          bureaus.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          <li>
            <a class="font-semibold underline underline-offset-4" href="https://www.identitytheft.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
              >IdentityTheft.gov</a
            >
            — recovery plan & documentation
          </li>
          <li>
            <a class="font-semibold underline underline-offset-4" href="https://reportfraud.ftc.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
              >ReportFraud.ftc.gov</a
            >
            — report scams and fraud
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          If money accounts are involved: change passwords, enable MFA, and contact your financial institutions using
          known-good contact methods (official app/website statements, not links in emails/texts).
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="cybercrime" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Cybercrime reporting</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900">
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          If you experienced a cyber-enabled crime (account takeover, scam, wire fraud, marketplace fraud, etc.), start
          with local law enforcement and also consider reporting through the official cybercrime reporting channels
          below.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          <li>
            <a class="font-semibold underline underline-offset-4" href="https://www.ic3.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
              >FBI Internet Crime Complaint Center (IC3)</a
            >
            — federal cybercrime complaint portal
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="state-resources" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">State resources (optional)</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900">
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          Many states maintain their own reporting portals, consumer protection pages, and cybersecurity guidance. Search
          your state name + “consumer protection” and your state name + “cyber crime reporting” for official links.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="crisis-support" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Crisis support (US)</h2>
      <div
        class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-6 text-amber-950 dark:border-amber-900/60 dark:bg-amber-950/40 dark:text-amber-100"
      >
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
          If you’re in immediate danger call <strong>911</strong>. If you need crisis support, these are official
          national resources:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li>
            <a class="font-semibold underline underline-offset-4" href="https://988lifeline.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
              >988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <a class="font-semibold underline underline-offset-4" href="https://www.thehotline.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
              >The National Domestic Violence Hotline</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="kids" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Families & kids</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900">
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          <li><strong>School info</strong>: avoid publicly posting schedules, teacher names, and pickup routines.</li>
          <li><strong>Photo safety</strong>: avoid house numbers, street signs, and identifying landmarks.</li>
          <li><strong>Talk about scams</strong>: local buy/sell group scams and “urgent payment” requests are common.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

